# Accepted exceptions - each is documented with full reasoning and a
# "what to change if your threat model differs" note in SECURITY_POSTURE.md.
# Everything not listed here is a hard CI failure.

# API Gateway access logging: Lambda logs cover request tracing at this scale
AVD-AWS-0001

# CloudWatch log group CMK: step-progress logs only, default SSE applies
AVD-AWS-0017

# DynamoDB CMK: run-status metadata; AWS-owned key at-rest encryption is on
AVD-AWS-0025

# Lambda X-Ray: durable executions have checkpoint-level tracing built in
AVD-AWS-0066

# S3 access logging: output bucket for published, public-by-intent artifacts
AVD-AWS-0089

# S3 CMK: SSE-S3 (AES256) is enabled; CMK is a consumer decision
AVD-AWS-0132
